body_html:
To make my seeing a little bit cleaner for you guys.
There is some IR format from opencv/dldt where many neural network models can be ported from different frameworks. Including those, which are not supported by onnx at the moment.
I want to write a compiler from IR format to caffe2 proto and use Caffe2 as an inference engine for NVIDIA GPUs. However, in Caffe2 some operations are missing, including those, which are necessary to run SSD models trained in Caffe and TF OD API.

body:
To make my seeing a little bit cleaner for you guys.
There is some IR format from opencv/dldt where many neural network models can be ported from different frameworks. Including those, which are not supported by onnx at the moment.
I want to write a compiler from IR format to caffe2 proto and use Caffe2 as an inference engine for NVIDIA GPUs. However, in Caffe2 some operations are missing, including those, which are necessary to run SSD models trained in Caffe and TF OD API.
